---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms and Conditions | Doctoral College UK" description="Terms and conditions governing the use of the Doctoral College UK website and the enrolment of students on DCUK programmes.">

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <p class="section-label mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Terms and Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Last updated: June 2026. These terms apply to all users of the DCUK website and to all students enrolled on DCUK programmes.</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-muted">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>These Terms and Conditions govern your use of the Doctoral College UK website (doctoralcollege.ac.uk) and your relationship with DCUK as a student, applicant, or visitor. By accessing this website or enrolling on a DCUK programme, you agree to be bound by these terms.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Doctoral College UK ("DCUK") is operated by [DCUK Legal Entity Name], registered in England and Wales. Our registered address is Suite 4, Cavendish House, 12 King Street, London, EC2V 8AJ.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">2. Use of the Website</h2>
          <p>You may use this website for lawful purposes only. You must not:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Use the site in any way that violates applicable law or regulation</li>
            <li>Transmit unsolicited communications or spam</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the site or its systems</li>
            <li>Use automated tools to scrape or download site content without our written permission</li>
            <li>Submit false or misleading information through any form or application</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">DCUK reserves the right to restrict or terminate access to the website at its discretion and without notice.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">3. Programme Enrolment and Student Obligations</h2>
          <p>Enrolment on a DCUK programme is subject to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Receipt and acceptance of a formal offer letter from DCUK</li>
            <li>Payment of the enrolment deposit as specified in the offer letter</li>
            <li>Provision of accurate and complete information throughout the application process</li>
            <li>Agreement to abide by DCUK's Academic Regulations, Code of Conduct, and all relevant policies</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">DCUK reserves the right to withdraw any offer or terminate enrolment if it is established that false or misleading information was provided during the application process.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">4. Fees and Payment</h2>
          <p>Programme fees are set out on our <a href="/fees" class="text-accent hover:underline">Fees page</a> and in your offer letter. By enrolling, you agree to pay the fees in accordance with the payment schedule agreed at enrolment.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Fees are non-refundable once a module or academic year has commenced, except in cases of:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Approved programme withdrawal within the first 14 days of the academic year</li>
            <li>Significant changes to the programme made by DCUK that materially affect your studies</li>
            <li>Extenuating circumstances reviewed and approved by the Director of Student Experience</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">DCUK reserves the right to suspend access to learning materials for students with outstanding fee balances.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">5. Academic Integrity</h2>
          <p>All work submitted for assessment must be your own original work unless otherwise specified. DCUK has a zero-tolerance policy on academic misconduct, including plagiarism, fabrication of data, and collusion. Suspected misconduct is investigated under our Academic Integrity Policy, and confirmed misconduct may result in programme termination.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">The use of AI-generated content in submitted work must be disclosed and used only in accordance with the guidance provided for each assessment. Undisclosed use of AI-generated content is treated as academic misconduct.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>All content on this website — including text, graphics, logos, and course materials — is the property of Doctoral College UK or its licensors and is protected by UK and international copyright law. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works without written permission.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Your own research, thesis, and submitted work remain your intellectual property. By submitting work for assessment, you grant DCUK a non-exclusive licence to use your work for quality assurance, archiving, and (with your permission) promotional or educational purposes.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>DCUK takes all reasonable steps to ensure the accuracy of information on this website but does not warrant that it is complete, current, or error-free. DCUK shall not be liable for any loss or damage arising from your use of the website or reliance on its content, except where such liability cannot be excluded by law.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Our total liability to any individual in connection with their use of DCUK services shall not exceed the total fees paid by that individual in the relevant academic year, except in cases of death, personal injury, or fraud.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">8. Changes to Programmes</h2>
          <p>DCUK reserves the right to make changes to programme content, structure, fees, and delivery methods. Where changes are material and affect enrolled students, DCUK will provide reasonable notice and work to mitigate any adverse impact. Students who are significantly disadvantaged by a change may be entitled to a pro-rata refund.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">9. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes arising from these terms or your use of DCUK services shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales, unless otherwise required by applicable consumer protection law.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">10. Contact</h2>
          <p>For queries about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">legal@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
